<div class="text" id="centre_col">
<p><a name="top"></a></p>
<h1>ESSUM23160 - Shares that may be awarded: Declarations from companies</h1>
<p>A statement on company headed paper signed by the company secretary is an acceptable declaration.  </p>
<p>If the shares to be used are not in the company establishing the plan, or that company is under the control of another company, the declaration should also show how the requirements of paragraphs 26 and 27 are satisfied.</p>
<p>The declaration given by a company may normally be accepted at face value, however Articles for companies which are not public limited companies (“PLCs”) (see <a href="ESSUM12100.htm">ESSUM12100</a>) will always be reviewed to ensure that is the case. It is accepted that shares of PLCs (see <a href="ESSUM12200.htm">ESSUM12200</a>) will normally satisfy the requirement. However, </p>
<ul>
<li>in cases of doubt,  or</li>
<li>if a company seeks reassurance that its shares satisfy the requirements, </li>
</ul>
<p>the scheme advisor should always obtain further information about the company and its shares and examine the facts in detail.  No concessions will be given if the requirements are not satisfied.</p>
